04$ to $0.1$ dex. FliPer values can be inserted in automatic global\nseismic pipelines to either give an estimation of the stellar surface gravity\nor to assess the quality of the seismic results by detecting any outliers in\nthe obtained $\\nu_{max}$ values. FliPer also constrain the surface gravities of\nmain-sequence dwarfs using only long cadence data for which the Nyquist\nfrequency is too low to measure the acoustic-mode properties.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 13 Sep 2018 18:00:05 GMT"}],"update_date":"2018-11-29"}
