ctly spherical, and thus the coupling between the\nfluid and the boundary does not vanish in the relevant limit of small\nviscosity.Moreover, the fully turbulent dissipation regime has not yet been\nreached in simulations.Our results suggest that the melted lunar core has been\nin a turbulent state throughout its history.Furthermore, in the view of recent\nexperimental results, we propose updated formulas predicting the fluid mean\nrotation vector and the associated dissipation in both the laminar and the\nturbulent regimes.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Fri, 14 Sep 2018 09:49:04 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Wed, 6 Feb 2019 11:08:29 GMT"}],"update_date":"2019-04-22"}
